What is IPv6 in AWS ? 

This is the successor to IPv4 as we are running out of their addresses 

→ IPv6 in AWS is public + internet routable ( no private range so secure it with SG + NACL + Firewalls )(same as IPv4) vs IPv4 there is private range 
→ 8 sections of 4 that range from 0-9 and A-F =[xxxx]:[xxxx]:[xxxx]:[xxxx]:[xxxx]:[xxxx]:[xxxx]:[xxxx]


IPv6 in Virtual private networks in AWS?

IPV4 cannot be disabled in you VPC and subnets 
+  But you can enable IPv6 ( Public IP addresses ) to operate in dual stack mode 

dual stack mode = both IPv4 and IPv6 are enabled 

→ Your EC2 Instances in a VPC will at least get a private internal IPv4 address and public IPv6 IP address 
→ EC2 instance (public and private IPv4/6 ) →  either can be used to communicate with internet gateway 

Examples :

EC2 private IPv4 →  NAT GW ( converts it to its own public IP address) →  internet gateway 
EC2 public IPv6 -> NATGW (no conversion as it’s public ) →  internet gateway 



IPv6 troubleshooting with EC2 instances ?

Trying to launch EC2 instance -> subnet (in VPC) and it’s not working 

→ This is because you always need an IPv4 IP address for you EC2 instance regardless of having a IPv6 address 
→ there’s no available IPv4 in your subnet 

Solution = Create a new IPv4 CIDR in your subnet 



Egress only Internet gateway IGW in AWS ?
Egress = traffic that’s leaving 

→ This adds an extra layer of security of security 
→ ensures unwanted traffic from WWW doesn’t reach IPv6 instances 

Inbound internet gateway - managed through security groups 
Outbound egress only internet gateway - only lets traffic leave and only IPv6 be used 

IPv4 traffic just use internet gateway 
IPv6 have the option of using egress only internet gateway for outbound traffic 

+ must update route tables *


